13 [[Edgar Cayce]], mysticist (born [[1877 in the United States|1877]])\n* January 7\n** [[Alexander Stirling Calder]], sculptor (born [[1870 in the United States|1870]])\n** [[Thomas McGuire]], fighter ace (born [[1920 in the United States|1920]]; killed in action)\n* January 13 \u2013 [[Margaret Deland]], novelist (born [[1857 in the United States|1857]])\n* January 22 \u2013 [[Blind Willie Johnson]], African American gospel singer and guitarist (born [[1897 in the United States|1897]]; pneumonia)\n* January 23 \u2013 [[Newton E. Mason]], U.S. Navy rear admiral (born [[1850 in the United States|1850]])\n* January 30 \u2013 [[Herbert L. Clarke]], cornet virtuoso (born [[1867 in the United States|1867]])\n* January 31 \u2013 [[Eddie Slovik]], soldier (born [[1920 in the United States|1920]]; executed for desertion)\n* February 2 \u2013 [[Joe Hunt]], tennis player (born [[1919 in the United States|1919]]; killed in naval aviation accident)\n* February 5 \u2013 [[Volga Hayworth]], showgirl (born c. 1898)\n* February 11 \u2013 [[Al Dubin]], songwriter (born 1891 in Switzerland)\n* March 4\n** [[Lucille La Verne]], actress (born [[1872 in the United States|1872]])\n** [[Mark Sandrich]], film director (born [[1900 in the United States|1900]])\n* March 30 \u2013 [[Maurice Rose]], U.S. Army general (born [[1899 in the United States|1899]]; killed in action)\n* March 31 \u2013 [[Harriet Boyd Hawes]], archaeologist (born [[1871 in the United States|1871]])\n* April 10 \u2013 [[Gloria Dickson]], actress (born [[1917 in the United States|1917]]; killed in domestic fire)\n* April 12 \u2013 [[Franklin D. Roosevelt]], 32nd [[President of the United States]] from 1933 to 1945 (born [[1882 in the United States|1882]])\n* April 17 \u2013 [[Ernie Pyle]], journalist (born [[1900 in the United States|1900]])\n* April 29 \u2013 [[Malcolm McGregor]], silent film actor (born [[1892 in the United States|1892]])\n* April 30 \u2013 [[William Orlando Darby]], U.S. Army colonel, creator of the Rangers (born [[1911 in the United States|1911]]; killed in action)\n* May 14 &ndash; [[Heber J. Grant]], 7th President of [[The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints]] (born [[1856 in the United States|1856]])\n* May 17 \u2013 [[Bobby Hutchins]], ''[[Our Gang]]'' films child actor (born [[1925 in the United States|1925]]; killed in military aviation accident)\n* May 18 \u2013 [[William Joseph Simmons]], founder of the second [[Ku Klux Klan]] (born [[1880 in the United States|1880]])\n* June 16 \u2013 [[Henry Bellamann]], author (born [[1882 in the United States|1882]])\n* June 18 \u2013 [[Simon Bolivar Buckner, Jr.]], U.S. Army general (born [[1886 in the United States|1886]]; killed in action at [[Battle of Okinawa]])\n* 20 June \u2013 [[Bruno Frank]], German author, poet, dramatist and humanist (born [[1887 in Germany|1887]])\n* July 13 \u2013 [[Alla Nazimova]], scriptwriter and actress (born 1879 in Crimea)\n* July 16 \u2013 [[Addison Randall]], Western film actor (born [[1906 in the United States|1906]])\n* July 25 \u2013 [[Charles Gilman Norris]], novelist (born [[1881 in the United States|1881]])\n* August 9 \u2013 [[Harry Hillman]], track athlete (born [[1881 in the United States|1881]])\n* August 10 \u2013 [[Robert H. Goddard]], rocket scientist (born [[1882 in the United States|1882]])\n* August 25 \u2013 [[Willis Augustus Lee]], U.S. Navy admiral and Olympic shooter (born [[1888 in the United States|1888]]; heart attack on active service)\n* September 1 \u2013 [[Frank Craven]], actor (born [[1881 in the United States|1881]])\n* September 6 \u2013 [[John S. McCain Sr.]], U.S. Navy admiral (born [[1884 in the United States|1884]]; heart attack on active service)\n* September 20 \u2013 [[Jack Thayer]], survivor of the [[Sinking of the RMS Titanic|sinking of the RMS ''Titanic'']] (born [[1894 in the United States|1894]])\n* September 26 \u2013 [[A. Peter Dewey]], soldier, first American casualty in [[Vietnam]] (born [[1916 in the United States|1916]])\