l links==\n* {{Commons category-inline}}\n\n{{US year nav}}\n{{Timeline of United States history}}\n{{North America topic|1945 in}}\n{{Year in Europe|1945}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:1945 In The United States}}\n[[Category:1945 in the United States| ]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|USA-related events during the year of 1945}}\n{{Yearbox US|1945}}\n\nEvents from the year '''1945 in the United States'''. [[World War II]] ended during this year following the surrender of [[Nazi Germany|Germany]] in May and that of [[Empire of Japan|Japan]] in September.\n\n{{TOC limit|2}}\n\n== Incumbents ==\n=== [[Federal government of the United States|Federal Government]] ===\n* [[President of the United States|President]]: [[Franklin D. Roosevelt]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|D]]-[[New York (state)|New York]]) (until April 12), [[Harry S. Truman]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|D]]-[[Missouri]]) (starting April 12)\n* [[Vice President of the United States|Vice President]]:\n** until January 20: [[Henry A. Wallace]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|D]]-[[Iowa]])\n** January 20\u2013April 12: [[Harry S. Truman]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|D]]-[[Missouri]])\n** starting April 12: ''vacant''\n* [[Chief Justice of the United States|Chief Justice]]: [[Harlan F. Stone]] ([[New York (state)|New York]])\n* [[Speaker of the United States House of Representatives|Speaker of the House of Representatives]]: [[Sam Rayburn]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|D]]-[[Texas]])\n* [[Senate Majority Leader]]: [[Alben W. Barkley]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|D]]-[[Kentucky]])\n* [[United States Congress|Congress]]: [[78th United States Congress|78th]] (until January 3), [[79th United States Congress|79th]] (starting January 3)\n\n{| class=\"wikitable collapsible collapsed\"\n! [[Governor (United States)|Governor]]s and [[Lieutenant governor (United States)|Lieutenant Governor]]s\n|-\n|\n=== Governors ===\n{{columns-list|colwidth=30em|\n* [[Governor of Alabama]]: [[Chauncey Sparks]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]]) \n* [[Governor of Arizona]]: [[Sidney Preston Osborn]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]]) \n* [[Governor of Arkansas]]: [[Homer Martin Adkins]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]]) (until January 9), [[Benjamin Travis Laney]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]]) (starting January 9)\n* [[Governor of California]]: [[Earl Warren]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]) \n* [[Governor of Colorado]]: [[John Charles Vivian]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]) \n* [[Governor of Connecticut]]: [[Raymond E. Baldwin]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]) \n* [[Governor of Delaware]]: [[Walter W. Bacon]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]) \n* [[Governor of Florida]]: [[Spessard Holland]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]]) (until January 2), [[Millard F. Caldwell]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]]) (starting January 2)\n* [[Governor of Georgia]]: [[Ellis Arnall]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]]) \n* [[Governor of Idaho]]: \n** until January 1: [[C. A. Bottolfsen]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]) \n** January 1-November 17: [[Charles C. Gossett]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]])\n** starting November 17: [[Arnold Williams (American politician)|Arnold Williams]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]])\n* [[Governor of Illinois]]: [[Dwight H. Green]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]) \n* [[Governor of Indiana]]: [[Henry F. Schricker]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]]) (until January 8), [[Ralph F. Gates]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]) (starting January 8) \n* [[Governor of Iowa]]: [[Bourke B. Hickenlooper]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]) (until January 11), [[Robert D. Blue]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]) (starting January 11)\n* [[Governor of Kansas]]: [[Andrew F. Schoeppel]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]) \n* [[Governor of Kentucky]]: [[Simeon S. Willis]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]) \n* [[Governor of Louisiana]]: [[Jimmie H. Davis]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]]) \n* [[Governor of Maine]]: [[Sumner Sewall]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]) (until January 3), [[Horace A. Hildreth]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]) (starting January 3)\n* [[Governor of Maryland]]: [[Herbert R. O'Conor]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]]) \n* [[Governor of Massachusetts]]: [[Leverett Saltonstall]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]) (until January 3), [[Maurice J. Tobin]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]]) (starting January 3)\n* [[Governor of Michigan]]: [[Harry Kelly (politician)|Harry Kelly]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]) \n* [[Governor of Minnesota]]: [[Edward John Thye]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]) \n* [[Governor of Mississippi]]: [[Thomas L. Bailey]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]]) \n* [[Governor of Missouri]]: [[Forrest C. Donnell]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]) (until January 8), [[Phil M. Donnelly]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]]) (starting January 8)\n* [[Governor of Montana]]: [[Sam C. Ford]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]) \n* [[Governor of Nebraska]]: [[Dwight Griswold]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]) \n* [[Governor of Nevada]]: [[Edward P. Carville]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]]) (until July 24), [[Vail M. Pittman]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]]) (starting July 24)\n* [[Governor of New Hampshire]]: [[Robert O. Blood]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]) (until January 4), [[Charles M. Dale]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]) (starting January 4)\n* [[Governor of New Jersey]]