rty (United States)|Democratic]]) (starting January 16)\n* [[Governor of Texas]]: [[Coke R. Stevenson]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]]) \n* [[Governor of Utah]]: [[Herbert B. Maw]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]]) \n* [[Governor of Vermont]]: [[William Henry Wills (politician)|William H. Wills]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]) (until January 4), [[Mortimer R. Proctor]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]) (starting January 4)\n* [[Governor of Virginia]]: [[Colgate Darden]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]]) \n* [[Governor of Washington]]: [[Arthur B. Langlie]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]) (until January 8), [[Monrad C. Wallgren]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]]) (starting January 8)\n* [[Governor of West Virginia]]: [[Matthew M. Neely]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]]) (until January 15), [[Clarence W. Meadows]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]]) (starting January 15)\n* [[Governor of Wisconsin]]: [[Walter S. Goodland]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]) \n* [[Governor of Wyoming]]: [[Lester C. Hunt]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]])\n}}\n\n=== Lieutenant Governors ===\n{{columns-list|colwidth=30em|\n* [[Lieutenant Governor of Alabama]]: [[Leven H. Ellis]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]]) \n* [[Lieutenant Governor of Arkansas]]: [[James Lavesque Shaver]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]])  \n* [[Lieutenant Governor of California]]: [[Frederick F. Houser]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]) \n* [[Lieutenant Governor of Colorado]]: [[William Eugene Higby]] [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]) \n* [[Lieutenant Governor of Connecticut]]: [[William L. Hadden]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]) (until month and day unknown), [[Charles Wilbert Snow]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]]) (starting month and 